{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 0, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "Commit", "identifier": ["microsoft", "vscode", "a2a8171b5876a08d62b52c01b6b44fce7eb0ea77"], "url": "https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/commit/a2a8171b5876a08d62b52c01b6b44fce7eb0ea77", "semantic_text": "feat: Add rate limiting to the API\n\nThis commit introduces rate limiting to the `/api/predict` endpoint using the `slowapi` library.\n\nKey changes:\n- Added `slowapi` to project dependencies.\n- Configured a global rate limiter for the FastAPI application, defaulting to 5 requests per minute per IP address.\n- Applied the rate limiter specifically to the `/api/predict` endpoint to prevent abuse and ensure fair usage of the model inference capabilities.\n- Added comprehensive tests for the rate limiting functionality, ensuring that requests within the limit are processed and requests exceeding the limit are correctly rejected with a 429 status code.\n- Updated `API.md` to document the new rate limiting feature.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1638991770.0}
